From 1edeef869eafedafe9fa6db30add0b3f9aea5671 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 07:21:12 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ci: add /admin/test-session + role=agent WS testKey bypass
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Lets external CI suites (the new @sira-screen-share/support-react-native
repo, others later) run real session loops without a human in the
dashboard. The CI process spins up an in-process WebRTC agent peer that
joins via the existing public WS — server stays a pure signaling relay,
no frame-storage logic added.

Both the admin endpoint and the WS bypass are gated by SIRA_TEST_KEY
(matched against the x-sira-test-key header / ?testKey= query). Leave
that env unset in production and both surfaces are inert.

Also extends @sira/shared additively for the native SDK's protocol
needs:
- new "frame" variant on StreamMsg (WebP base64 payload)
- optional "platform" on viewport
- optional "sessionType" on JoinSessionResponse
- relaxes JoinSessionRequest.origin from URL to opaque string so native
  bundle IDs (com.example.app) validate

All changes are backward compatible: existing web SDK + dashboard fields
are untouched, optional additions default to web behavior.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
